## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-102"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> è l'oggetto principale che implementa la tecnologia di semantica nel Speech.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-102"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> is the primary object that implements the semantic technology in System.Speech.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="07988-103">Interpretazione semantica consente grammatiche definire le regole per l'uso da un motore di riconoscimento di interpretare correttamente l'input audio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-103">Semantic interpretation allows grammars to define rules for use by a recognition engine to correctly interpret audio input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="07988-104">Interpretazione semantica consente inoltre di motori di riconoscimento organizzare i risultati in modo che possono essere più facilmente elaborati, anziché restituire riconosciuto solo parole e le sequenze di parole.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-104">Semantic interpretation also enables recognition engines to organize their results so that they can be more easily processed, rather than returning only recognized words and sequences of words.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-105">Ad esempio, il motore di riconoscimento di output "Modificato in background in rosso" dovrà essere analizzati e interpretati da un'applicazione prima che è stato possibile intervenire.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-105">For example, the recognition engine output "Change background to red" would have to be parsed and interpreted by an application before it could be acted upon.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="07988-106">Oggetto <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> oggetto può specificare un'interpretazione semantica per velocizzare l'elaborazione più chiara, specificando che la frase ha due sottostrutture semantiche, uno per la selezione in background o in primo piano (rappresentato dal testo "background") e l'altro per la selezione colore (rappresentato dal testo "red").</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-106">A <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object can specify a semantic interpretation to make processing clearer by specifying that the phrase has two semantic substructures, one for selecting background or foreground (represented by the text "background"), and the other for selecting color (represented by the text "red").</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-107">Speech rappresenta la semantica di un'operazione di riconoscimento in un albero di <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> oggetti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-107">System.Speech represents the semantics of a recognition operation in a tree of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> objects.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-108">Ogni <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> istanza include quanto segue:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-108">Each <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instance includes the following:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="07988-109">Un' <xref:System.Object>, a cui si accede tramite il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> proprietà, utilizzata per la chiave di istanza del <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-109">An <xref:System.Object>, accessed by means of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> property, used to key the instance of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue>.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="07988-110">Una misura dell'accuratezza dell'analisi semantica, restituito dal <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A> proprietà.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-110">A measure of the accuracy of semantic parsing, returned by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="07988-111">Una raccolta di coppie nome/valore (<xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602>) di oggetti figlio che sono anche <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> istanze.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-111">A collection of name/value pairs (<xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602>) of child objects, which are also <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instances.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="07988-112">I nodi figlio sono accessibili tramite il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> implementazione di <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary%602> utilizzando una chiave di ricerca di stringa e un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> istanza, come nell'esempio seguente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-112">Child nodes are accessible through the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> implementation of <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary%602> using a string lookup key and a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instance, as in the following example.</span></span>  
  
    ```csharp  
    foreach (KeyValuePair<String, SemanticValue> child in semantics)   
    {  
      Utils.CreateSemanticsTreeNodes(semanticsNode.Nodes, child.Value, child.Key);  
    }  
    ```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-113">Motori di riconoscimento basati Speech forniscono istanze valide di <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> per tutto l'output dal riconoscimento, anche per le frasi con struttura alcuna semantica esplicita.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-113">Recognition engines based on System.Speech provide valid instances of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> for all output from recognition, even for phrases with no explicit semantic structure.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-114">Il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> dell'istanza per una frase viene ottenuta usando il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Semantics%2A> proprietà le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> oggetto (o gli oggetti che ereditano da essa, ad esempio <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-114">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instance for a phrase is obtained using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Semantics%2A> property on the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> object (or objects that inherit from it, such as <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-115"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> gli oggetti ottenuti per ottenere frasi riconosciute senza struttura semantica sono caratterizzati da:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-115"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> objects obtained for recognized phrases without semantic structure are characterized by:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="07988-116">La mancanza di elementi figlio (<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Count%2A> è 0).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-116">The lack of children (<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Count%2A> is 0).</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="07988-117">La proprietà <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> è `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-117">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> property is `null`.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="07988-118">Un livello di confidenza semantica artificiali pari a 1,0 (restituito da <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A>).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-118">An artificial semantic confidence level of 1.0 (returned by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A>).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-119">In genere, le applicazioni creano <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> istanze indirettamente, aggiungerli alla <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> gli oggetti utilizzando <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultValue> e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultKey> istanze, in combinazione con <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices> e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> oggetti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-119">Typically, applications create <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instances indirectly, adding them to <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objects by using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultValue> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultKey> instances,  in conjunction with  <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objects.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-120">Indirizzare la costruzione di un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> istanza è utile durante la creazione della grammatica fortemente tipizzata.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-120">Direct construction of a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instance is useful during the creation of strongly-typed grammars.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-121"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> implementa il <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary%602>, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.ICollection%601>, e <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601> interfacce.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-121"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> implements the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary%602>, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.ICollection%601>, and <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601> interfaces.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-122">Nell'esempio seguente viene illustrato un gestore per un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized> evento progettato per gestire i comandi per modificare il colore primo piano e sfondo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-122">The following example shows a handler for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized> event designed to handle commands to change foreground and background color.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-123">Il gestore identifica riconosciute frasi che non presentano alcuna struttura di semantica sottostante grazie al rilevamento di un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Count%2A> pari a zero e un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> di `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-123">The handler identifies recognized phrases that have no underlying semantic structure by detecting a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Count%2A> of zero and a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> of `null`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="07988-124">Questo output di riconoscimento viene quindi elaborato direttamente per l'analisi del testo non elaborato.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-124">This recognition output is then processed directly by parsing the raw text.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-125">In altri casi, il gestore Usa chiavi per ottenere i componenti RGB di un nome di colore, per determinare se il comando modificherà la foreground o background o per indicare che è stata trovata alcuna chiave valida.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-125">In other cases, the handler uses keys to obtain the RGB components of a color name, to determine whether the command will change the foreground or background, or to indicate that no valid key was found.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
newGrammar.SpeechRecognized +=  
  delegate(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs eventArgs)   
  {  
  
    // Retrieve the value of the semantic property.  
    bool changeBackGround = true;  
    string errorString = "";  
    SemanticValue semantics = eventArgs.Result.Semantics;  
  
    Color newColor = Color.Empty;  
  
    try   
    {  
      if (semantics.Count == 0 && semantics.Value==null)  
      {  
        // Signifies recognition by a grammar with no semantics.  
        // Parse the string, assuming that the last word is color,  
        // and search for "background" or "foreground" in the input.  
        if (eventArgs.Result.Text.Contains("foreground"))   
        {  
          changeBackGround = false;  
        }  
        string cName = eventArgs.Result.Words[eventArgs.Result.Words.Count - 1].Text;  
        newColor = Color.FromName(cName);  
  
      }  
      else if (semantics.ContainsKey("colorStringList") ^ semantics.ContainsKey("colorRGBValueList"))   
      {  
  
        // Determine whether to change background or foreground.  
        if (semantics.ContainsKey("applyChgToBackground"))   
        {  
          changeBackGround = semantics["applyChgToBackground"].Value is bool;  
        }  
  
        // Get the RGB color value.  
        if (semantics.ContainsKey("colorStringList"))   
        {  
          newColor = Color.FromName((string)semantics["colorStringList"].Value);  
        }  
        if (semantics.ContainsKey("colorRGBValueList"))   
        {  
          newColor = System.Drawing.Color.FromArgb((int)semantics["colorRGBValueList"].Value);  
        }  
      }  
      else   
      {  
  
        // Throw an exception if the semantics do not contain the keys we  
        // support.  
        throw(new Exception("Unsupported semantics keys found."));  
      }  
    }  
  
    catch (Exception exp)   
    {  
      MessageBox.Show(String.Format("Unable to process color semantics.:\n{0}\n", exp.Message));  
      return;  
    }  
  
    // Change colors, either foreground or background.  
    if (changeBackGround)   
    {  
      BackColor = newColor;  
      float Bright = BackColor.GetBrightness();  
      float Hue = BackColor.GetHue();  
      float Sat = BackColor.GetSaturation();  
  
      // Make sure that text is readable regardless of the background.  
      if (BackColor.GetBrightness() <= .50)   
      {  
        ForeColor = Color.White;  
      }  
      else   
      {  
        ForeColor = Color.Black;  
      }  
    }  
    else   
    {  
      ForeColor = newColor;  
      float Bright = ForeColor.GetBrightness();  
      float Hue = ForeColor.GetHue();  
      float Sat = ForeColor.GetSaturation();  
  
      // Make sure that text is readable regardless of Foreground.  
      if (ForeColor.GetBrightness() <= .50)   
      {  
        BackColor = Color.White;  
      }  
      else   
      {  
        BackColor = Color.Black;  
      }  
    }  
    return;  
  };  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-143">Il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> proprietà, che restituisce una misura della correttezza dell'analisi semantica, non deve essere confuso con il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> proprietà, che restituisce una misura dell'accuratezza del riconoscimento vocale.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-143">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property, which returns a measure of the correctness of semantic parsing, should not be confused with the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property, which returns a measure of the accuracy of speech recognition.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-144">Nell'esempio seguente viene usato per ricorsivo e quindi visualizzare le informazioni (incluse confidenza) come un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection>, o come i nodi che compongono la struttura ad albero della semantica utilizzata per riconoscere una frase.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-144">The following example is used to recursively traverse and then display information (including confidence) as a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TreeNodeCollection>, or as the nodes making up the tree structure of the semantics used to recognize a phrase.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
internal static void CreateSemanticsTreeNodes(  
        TreeNodeCollection nodes,  
        SemanticValue semantics,  
        String name)   
{  
  string semanticsText =   
      String.Format("  {0}  (Confidence {1})", name,semantics.Confidence);  
  
  // Format integers as hexadecimal.  
  if (semantics.Value == null )  
  {  
    semanticsText = semanticsText + " = null";  
  }  
  else if (semantics.Value.GetType() == typeof(int))   
  {  
    semanticsText = String.Format("{0} = {1:X} ", semanticsText, semantics.Value);  
  }   
  else   
  {  
    semanticsText = semanticsText + " = " + semantics.Value.ToString();  
  }  
  
  TreeNode semanticsNode = new TreeNode(semanticsText);  
  foreach (KeyValuePair<String, SemanticValue> child in semantics)   
  {  
    CreateSemanticsTreeNodes(semanticsNode.Nodes, child.Value, child.Key);  
  }  
  nodes.Add(semanticsNode);  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-152">È possibile accedere solo i dati dal valore di chiave in fase di esecuzione, ad esempio per controllare *semantici ["myKey"]. Valore*, e ciò genera un'eccezione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-152">You can only access data by key value at runtime, for example to check *semantic["myKey"].Value*, and this generates an exception.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="07988-153">Si consiglia di eseguire la query di oggetto con <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.ContainsKey%2A> prima di usare <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Item%2A> con una determinata istanza di <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-153">We recommend that you query the object with <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.ContainsKey%2A> before using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Item%2A> with a given instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-154">Nell'esempio seguente viene illustrato un gestore per un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized> evento progettato per gestire i comandi per modificare il colore primo piano e sfondo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-154">The following example shows a handler for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized> event designed to handle commands to change foreground and background color.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="07988-155">Dopo avere gestito frasi che vengono riconosciute, ma non presentano alcuna struttura Semantic Model, il gestore verifica la presenza delle chiavi appropriate utilizzando <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.ContainsKey%2A> (`applyChgToBackground`, `colorRGBValueList`, o `colorStringList)`e quindi elabora i dati organizzati semanticamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="07988-155">After handling phrases that are recognized but have no semantic structure, the handler checks for the presence of appropriate keys using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.ContainsKey%2A> (`applyChgToBackground`, `colorRGBValueList`, or `colorStringList)`,  and then processes the semantically organized data.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
newGrammar.SpeechRecognized +=  
  delegate(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs eventArgs)   
  {  
  
    // Retrieve the value of the semantic property.  
    bool changeBackGround = true;  
    string errorString = "";  
    SemanticValue semantics = eventArgs.Result.Semantics;  
  
    Color newColor = Color.Empty;  
  
    try   
    {  
      if (semantics.Count == 0 && semantics.Value==null)  
      {  
  
